Data has over   	  90k records, 12 categories under Risk title and 20k categories under Risk description.    Sentiment Analysis on Audit data   Set examples of positive, negative and neutral sentences according to audit domain.   Built N gram data - removed sparsity in data  - build models Naïve Bayes, Decision Tree  Built N gram data - feature selection on data (extracting features that contribute more) - built model Naïve Bayes  Built N gram data - POS tagging on data - build model Naïve Bayes,  This approach gave better accuracy.  Libraries Used : StanfordNLP, lingpipe, openNLP, nltk and custom algorithms  Technologies Used : Java, NLP, and Machine Learning  Algorithms Used : k means, Naïve Bayes, KNN, LDA, POS tagging, parsing algos,     I-Quotient (Start Up Company : services focused on Data Science and Big Data Analytics)  Data Analyst		Sep-2014 to March-2016  ROLES and RESPONSIBILITIES :   	    Brand Performance : Objective of the project is to perform comparison between a Brand and other Brands (as its competitor) w.r.t the survey data to determine who the Best Brand is.   Pre Processing : Analyzed and explored complex data sets that consisted of multiple data types with more than 25 factor levels for few columns. Exploration of data sets in R. Preprocessing of Data such as deriving new attributes, sub setting records based on attributes. Lapply functions  Performed Significance Testing and generated outputs. T test statistic on pre processed data for every specific brand / subset to compare performance with other brands. Integrated R Studio with Tibco Spotfire. Generated Significance Output in the Spotfire Dashboard.  Worked under multiple projects of BFSI, Health Care, and Retail domain currently.  Built Recommendation Engine for products and applied Associative Rules for patter mining.  Prediction of Credit Card fraudulence : Cooking of Data, Pre Processing of Data, Modeling, Prediction and Accuracy improvement.     Technologies and Tools using : Technologies and Fields using : Programming languages : R, Python	  Machine Learning, Statistics  Hadoop, Cassandra, Pig	  Hadoop, Cassandra, Pig  Visualization Tools : Tableau
